#   DIS tickets: cross-cutting spec/impl discrepancies

DIS collects spec↔implementation discrepancies that cut across verbs; a gap found mid-fix gets its own DIS ticket, linked both ways. Each entry below is one open ticket with its live state; a landed one (verify with `be log | grep DIS-NNN`) drops off. The 21 below remain open. The fix-and-land method is [Issues].

##  Active tickets

 -  [DIS-001] — sha-bearing wtlog row-0 anchor; correctness landed, only the optional clone-path cleanup remains.
 -  [DIS-002] — `be patch` over a transport drops freshly-fetched commits; routing landed, still loses the added file.
 -  [DIS-003] — WEAVEMerge token identity is positional, not total; one sub-bug fixed, a clean diff-key fix stays constrained.
 -  [DIS-004] — delete's dirty gate is mtime-only, with no `--force` content double-check bypass.
 -  [DIS-005] — sha1/projector single-scheme URI grammar: document the two-step `be head` then `be sha1://` remote read.
 -  [DIS-006] — `be get file:` from a legacy elided store: migrate-in-place vs materialize-on-clone undecided.
 -  [DIS-007] — magic refs `?null` / `?back` are unimplemented.
 -  [DIS-008] — GET `#~N` commit-ancestor rewind operator is unimplemented.
 -  [DIS-011] — `be put ssh://host/path` without `?ref` force-pushes instead of logging.
 -  [DIS-019] — direct `be post ssh://…/<sub>` forges a funny `refs/heads/.beagle/` ref.
 -  [DIS-021] — wpush debug spew is on by default; a pack is built on error; the have-set is unused.
 -  [DIS-022] — `be log` is empty in a detached or submodule worktree.
 -  [DIS-023] — `be` status is non-idempotent: a re-run hides real modifications.
 -  [DIS-024] — flat→sharded store-layout migration; retire the top-level `.be/refs`.
 -  [DIS-025] — `be patch` squash bases on the target's PARENT (silent data loss); Stage 1 landed, resolver redesign open.
 -  [DIS-029] — MARK renders bare-indent divs as raw `<p>` text and merges across the depth boundary.
 -  [DIS-031] — POST provenance from a trailing `!` (refer/forget); `post!` = --force; ban messages ending in `!`.
 -  [DIS-032] — bring the PATCH/POST/URI/Verbs specs in line with the bang model.
 -  [DIS-039] — bare `be get` is a status no-op per GET.mkd but the Issues loop assumes it FFs; the specs contradict.
 -  [DIS-040] — POSTCFLCT can't be de-falsed at the byte level; needs a provenance check, couples to POST-016.
 -  [DIS-042] — cur's divergent commit: `be patch <peer>` + `be post` replays onto peer, drops cur's bytes (Invariant 2).
 -  [DIS-044] — WEAVEMerge's RGA tie-break sorts concurrent siblings by raw commit-id DESC, not causally — real (non-monotonic) hashlets strand replace-edits / splice clean instead of conflicting (silent merge data-loss). Fixed: tie-break on the causal commit index + topo-deterministic commits[]; fuzzer off its monotonic-id oracle. Landed `5041ed18`.
 -  [DIS-045] — CLOSING: premise false. Engine already correct ([[DIS-043]] idh JOIN + [[DIS-044]] causal order removed both DIS-003 layers); no repro in 4.7M fuzz. Committed `711618fe` (pure teeth: WEAVE03 step-2 oracle + blank criss-cross cases + `W2_BLANK` fuzz; 322/322). `be-patch-15` 5/5 fail re-tasked to [[DOG-005]] — graf cut-over glue, not the engine.

DIS-043 (dog/WEAVE concurrent-insert order path-dependent — criss-cross duplication;
fixed with an RGA stable-order key: a per-token `'A'` anchor column + identity merge-JOIN
in commit-id RGA order) landed `8eece3f3`; `dog/test/WEAVE01` + the DWEAVE fuzz corpus.

